comment:
* Simple class for handling serialized USet/UnicodeSet structures
 * without object creation. See ICU4C icu/source/common/uset.c.
 *
 * @hide Only a subset of ICU is exposed in Android
 * @hide draft / provisional / internal are hidden on Android

methods.name: public final boolean getSet(char[] src, int srcStart)
methods.comment:
* Fill in the given serialized set object.
     * @param src pointer to start of array
     * @param srcStart pointer to start of serialized data (length value)
     * @return true if the given array is valid, otherwise false

methods.name: public final void setToOne(int c)
methods.comment:
* Set the USerializedSet to contain the given character (and nothing
     * else).

methods.name: public final boolean getRange(int rangeIndex, int[] range)
methods.comment: * Returns a range of characters contained in the given serialized * set. * @param rangeIndex a non-negative integer in the range 0.. * getSerializedRangeCount()-1 * @param range variable to receive the data in the range * @return true if rangeIndex is valid, otherwise false

methods.name: public final boolean contains(int c)
methods.comment:
* Returns true if the given USerializedSet contains the given
     * character.
     * @param c the character to test for
     * @return true if set contains c

methods.name: public final int countRanges()
methods.comment:
* Returns the number of disjoint ranges of characters contained in
     * the given serialized set.  Ignores any strings contained in the
     * set.
     * @return a non-negative integer counting the character ranges
     * contained in set

methodNames: public final boolean getSet(char[] src, int srcStart)
public final boolean getRange(int rangeIndex, int[] range)
